@charlenni I see there is an issue with the compilation:
https://jenkins.mono-project.com/blue/organizations/jenkins/SkiaSharp-Pulls/detail/SkiaSharp-Pulls/130/pipeline

```
../../../src/c/sk_drawable.cpp: In function 'void sk_drawable_draw(sk_drawable_t*, sk_canvas_t*, const sk_matrix_t*)':
../../../src/c/sk_drawable.cpp:33:54: error: taking address of temporary [-fpermissive]
     AsDrawable(d)->draw(AsCanvas(c), &AsMatrix(matrix));
                                                      ^
```

You may have to copy the matrix to a local variable:

```cpp
SkMatrix m = AsMatrix(matrix);
AsDrawable(d)->draw(AsCanvas(c), m);
```

@mattleibow That's very strange, because, if I compile Skia on my machine, I don't have any problems.

I now removed the ````const```` before matrix parameter. Hope, that this removes the error. Could not test it (see above).

Removed the test from sample project.
